<HEADLINE>
COMMENTARY: ALPHA MALE'S E-MAIL 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By MAUREEN DOWD    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ As the cherry blossoms shimmered in the sun on
Friday, the capital was in a black tizzy.
</P>
<P>
   It was like a bad dream _ more vanishing Clinton White House
records, more congressional and Justice Department investigations
and, worst of all, more Dan Burton.
</P>
<P>
   The bargain-basement Torquemada of the House Republicans was
once more truffle-hunting for White House turpitude, vowing that he
would not rest until he discovered whether the abuse of power that
now confronts us is ``a glitch or an intentional glitch.''
</P>
<P>
   He is having hearings on why the White House couldn't find a
huge number of e-mails _ on subjects likely to include the '96
campaign finance scandal and Monica Lewinsky _ thousands to and
from the vice president's office.
</P>
<P>
   W. gleefully demanded to know why the Inventor of the Internet
was lost in cyberspace.
</P>
<P>
   Then, late last night, something incredible happened. A basket
of e-mail printouts was found on Janet Reno's doorstep. (The FBI is
checking reports that a man, about 6'1'', with a stiff gait and
wearing earth tones, was seen skulking away.) The basket was a
treasure trove, vouchsafing the attorney general a peek at the vice
president's hard drive:
</P>
<P>
   From: Gore(at)Veepworld.com
</P>
<P>
   To: Hsia(at)Buddhistemple.com
</P>
<P>
   Date: Sat, 30 Mar 1996
</P>
<P>
   Maria:
</P>
<P>
   I'm looking forward to the Non-Finance-Related, Community
Outreach Event you are planning. My goodness, it will be a relief
to find some serenity in the Non-Finance-Related company of you and
your monks. We do not live on material things alone. We'll just
burn some incense and get some Non-Finance-Related karma going.
</P>
<P>
   _Al
</P>
<P>
   From: Gore(at)Veepworld.com
</P>
<P>
   To: editors(at)nytimes.com
</P>
<P>
   Date: Tue, 4 Mar 1997
</P>
<P>
   Would you please run a correction on today's front-page story?
What I said was, ``know patrolling eagle priority.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Al
</P>
<P>
   From: Gore(at)Veepworld.com
</P>
<P>
   To: McCain(at)Senate.com
</P>
<P>
   Date: Wed, 1 Oct 1997
</P>
<P>
   John: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   I am your bill's biggest fan. I HATE MONEY. Here's some straight
talk, John: Every time I sit down with a $100,000 donor, I want
nothing more than to close my eyes and find myself curled up with a
copy of ``Walden.'' I HATE MONEY.
</P>
<P>
   _Al
</P>
<P>
   From: Gore(at)Veepworld.com
</P>
<P>
   To: Gore(at)Home&AMP;hearth.com
</P>
<P>
   Date: Wed, 14 Jan 1998
</P>
<P>
   Karenna:
</P>
<P>
   Whether or not I ever get to be president, know that I am in
politics to fight for women. And not just women 18-34. Also women
35-49. Also women, 50-still breathing. Soccer moms, waitress moms
and Medicare grannies _ I love 'em all.
</P>
<P>
   And I'm thinking outside the box here, but wouldn't it be just
terrific if Congress had a Catholic chaplain? Anyway, these are
idle thoughts.
</P>
<P>
   _love, Dad
</P>
<P>
   From: Gore(at)Veepworld.com
</P>
<P>
   To: JReno(at)Seenoevil.com
</P>
<P>
   Date: Thu, 6 Aug 1998
</P>
<P>
   Madame Attorney General:
</P>
<P>
   I want you to know that I expect nothing but the most vigorous
investigation of my conduct in '96. Don't spare my feelings. Don't
worry about my future. Ambition isn't everything. I would welcome
the scrutiny of a special prosecutor. Your campaign finance task
force can poke into any nook and cranny. My phone logs are your
phone logs. My call sheets are your call sheets. Hit me with your
best shot! Money is soft, but justice is hard.
</P>
<P>
   _Al
</P>
<P>
   From: Gore(at)Veepworld.com
</P>
<P>
   To: Potus(at)Westwing.com
</P>
<P>
   Date: Sat, 19 Dec 1998
</P>
<P>
   Bill:
</P>
<P>
   Stop your blubbering. I will fall on your sword. I will attend
the Rose Garden rally after the impeachment vote, and read
Blumenthal's line about your being ``one of our greatest
presidents.''
</P>
<P>
   But I have to level with you. As a perfectly virtuous husband, I
am disappointed. As a perfectly virtuous politician, I am
disappointed. As a perfectly virtuous American, I am disappointed.
Disappointed. Disappointed. Disappointed.
</P>
<P>
   _Al
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
