<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KASHMIR-SHOOTOUT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INDIAN FORCES KILL 5 SUSPECTED IN SIKH MASSACRE 
</HEADLINE>
  (jw) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   JAMMU, Kashmir _ In a shootout with Islamic militants Saturday,
Indian soldiers killed at least five men suspected in the killing
of 35 Sikhs in Kashmir last week week.
</P>
<P>
   Soldiers cordoned off Pacharthan Pathribal, a village 50 miles
south of Srinagar, and opened fire on a pair of houses where seven
militants were believed to be hiding, police said. The militants
returned fire, and in a two-hour gun battle five rebels were
killed.
</P>
<P>
   Police later blew up the houses where the two remaining
militants were hiding, but did not immediately know whether they
escaped or were killed.
</P>
<P>
   The government has identified Hizbul Mujahedeen, one of a dozen
groups fighting to separate Kashmir from India, as one of two rebel
organizations responsible for the massacre of villagers in Chati
Singhpura, about five miles from Pacharthan Pathribal.
</P>
<P>
   Kashmir's director general of police, Gurbachan Jagat, said
information that led the authorities to the militants' hideout was
provided by a member of Hizbul Mujahedeen.
</P>
<P>
   Jagat said the militants appeared to be foreigners.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is certain that they were the killers,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   In the massacre on Monday, gunmen shot 35 Sikh men after
separating them from the rest of the villagers. The shootings took
place as President Clinton was about to begin a state visit to
India, with the declared objective of trying to reduce tensions
between India and Pakistan. Kashmir is divided between the two
nations, with both claiming the Himalayan territory in its
entirety.
</P>
<P>
   In another episode, suspected militants shot and killed five
people in Budan, 120 miles north of Jammu, the winter capital of
Indian-controlled Kashmir, late on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the militants entered two adjoining houses in the
village and began firing at the residents. Two men and three women
were killed. Three people were seriously hurt.
</P>
<P>
   The militants later escaped into a nearby forest, police said.
</P>
<P>
   No group has claimed responsibility for the attack, police said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
