<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0325: AFRICA'S AIDS ORPHANS -- In sub-Saharan
Africa, 23.3 million people are infected with HIV/AIDS. The disease
is destroying entire villages, but beyond that it is robbing these
countries of a whole generation of potentially productive people.
Perhaps the most grim by-product is the staggering fact that the
disease has created more than 10 million orphans a number that is
expected to soar to 13 million next year. The implications of this
are devastating. (Roughton, Cox News Service). Art includes a
5-column color illustration showing the devastation to the African
continent, a 2-column color photo of a 12-year-old girl who is
suddenly thrust into the role of mother after her parents died of
AIDS, a 1-column color photo of an 88-year-old woman who must now
take responsibility for her grandchildren.
