   OPED/EDITORIAL
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ The conservative majority of the U.S. Supreme
Court did congressional Republicans no favor when it held that the
federal Food and Drug Administration lacks the authority to
regulate tobacco as a drug. Though it was certainly not the
justices' intention to do so, the ruling hands Democrats another
big-stick issue with which to pound Republicans in this especially
crucial election year. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for
Cox Newspapers.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ MIAMI _ The decision of a federal judge in
the custody case of little Elian Gonzalez has once again stirred
passions. At any moment the exile community is expected to tie up
Miami's streets with protests that will challenge the relationship
between the exile-dominated local government and those of us who
just want to be able to drive to the store. (Howard Kleinberg is a
columnist for Cox News Service.) MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
