HABITAT _ Throughout the Phoenix area, dusty beds of barren rivers
and streams are being turned into wildlife habitats in a flurry of
activity not seen since forests of cottonwoods and willows
disappeared from the Salt River. The success of Tempe's 224-acre
Town Lake and Gilbert's 110-acre riparian preserve has swayed
critics who felt the creation of desert wetlands wasted precious
water. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MENTAL _ When Gae Juline, 59, and her husband, Jeff, tried to get
help for Kenny, already diagnosed in two other states as
schizophrenic, they didn't realize the resistance he would face in
being declared seriously mentally ill in Arizona. In August, when
Kenny tried to get into Arizona's mental health system, he was
among the 86 percent turned down last year by ValueOptions, a
for-profit company hired by Arizona to provide mental health
services for the Valley's poor. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BOMB _A Chandler man was nearly killed Saturday when a package
exploded in his dining room, tearing off one of his fingers and
ripping holes through nearby ceilings and walls. Neighbors said
Richard Simer, 50, a Revlon employee, found a package addressed to
him in his driveway when he picked up his newspaper, but Chandler
police said they heard conflicting stories. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
